{"block": {"feedback_wrong": "", "subtitles": {}, "animation": null, "name": "text", "text": "Also, it is cool to note that the nature of Depth First Search's exploration makes implementing the algorithm recursively absurdly simple. Take a look at this pseudcode:<br><p></p><pre><code class=\"cpp\"><b>DFSRecursion(s): //where s is the starting vertex\n</b>    mark s as explored \n\u2003\u2003\u2003\u2003for each unexplored neighbor v of s:\n\u2003\u2003\u2003\u2003\u2003\u2003\u2003\u2003DFSRecursion(v) </code></pre><p></p><p>Notice that declaring/using a stack is not needed since the recursive nature of the algorithm provides the stack implementation for us. <br></p><p><b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-red\">STOP and Think:</span></b> It is important to note that there does not exist such a simple recursive pseudocode for Breath First Search; why might this be the case?<br></p>", "tests_archive": null, "source": null, "subtitle_files": [], "options": {}, "feedback_correct": "", "video": null}, "id": "116288", "time": "2016-09-06T23:45:53.866734"}